summary: can anyone confirm that the lookback happens in real life?
body:
can anyone confirm that the lookback happens in real life?

cuz uhm i can?? the lookback is literally 100% real if you have a crush on someone. see lately i’ve been like crushing on this guy who i never expected myself to like and it’s weird. i didn’t notice it until yesterday. i’m finding myself taking different routes to class hoping to see him. see likeee he likes me too , and always has?? LOL it’s really complicated.


when the lookback happened: the first time it happened.. he walked me to spanish class and we said bye and didn’t hug which i found odd. i looked back at him without even thinking about it and DID IT AGAIN and then he was like “alrii come here” and we hugged goodbyeee. it happened again today. seeeee i ran into him in the hallway (whenever we see each other, we just gotta be touching in SOME way) so yeahhh we like extended our arms to initiate a greeting (weird shit lmaoo).. anyways we walked passed each other afterwards and both turned around to look at each otherrr. AND LIKE WE WERE BOTH BLUSHING LMFJKSOCJSKNSKS. i was like “whhhhattt omggg” and idkkk cute shit. he makes me wanna write one-shots and make one of those instagram video edits of us.

summary: I love how Cyrus went from "I hate  TJ, who's TJ?" and "He's a lot meaner looking outside" to now being "That's just his face"...
question: I love how Cyrus went from "I hate  TJ, who's TJ?" and "He's a lot meaner looking outside" to now being "That's just his face" and biting his lip everytime TJ gives him puppy dog eyes
answer: cyrus is such a good boy. he only “hated” tj initially out of solidarity and support for his best friend but then he was still willing to get to know this guy and understand him when nobody else has ever taken the time to do that and ugh :( i love my bois
